DRAGON hostname: dragon.local
- u: dragon
- p: dragon

pigpio daemon has been installed to remove servo jitter
install location: /etc/systemd/system/pigpiod.service

virtual environment on pi where packages are installed can be activated with: source /home/dragon/Documents/dragon/DRAGON-Teather/COM/venv/bin/activate

**To vnc into Pi to update code, both laptop and Pi need to be tethered or on the same private wifi network (like a phone hotspot)**


GROUND CONTROL SYSTEM (on laptop)

Libraries are installed on a seperate conda environment called "gcs"
- conda activate gcs





***STARTUP INSTRUCTIONS:***
- Power on Pi
- Connect tether, ensure green lights on amplifier
- Wait several minutes for pi to boot, meanwhile turn on game controller and ensure it connects to laptop
- On laptop, open TigerVCN
- Connect to VCN server: dragon.local  using username: dragon  and password: dragon
- Through VCN on Pi, open terminal and startup_commands.txt
- Copy-paste and run startup commands in Pi terminal. Wait a few seconds until it says "Sender running"
- Open laptop terminal and copy-paste the following commands:

conda activate gcs
cd Dragon-Teather-COM/
python dragon_gcs.py

- Fullscreen the GCS, click anywhere on the screen to select the window, and press 'Enter'
- GCS should now be running and connected
